    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but i've been reading some critiques that say originalism is just a way for judges to push a specific political agenda under the guise of being \"neutral.\" how would an originalist respond to the idea that their method is actually just a tool for conservative outcomes?",
      "source": "evaluator"
